Let‚Äôs talk about breath and static muscle preparation for hang snatch above knee. First, breathe in to stabilize thorax and engage back and core before bringing the barbell to your hip position. Relax your arms and then lower the barbell with control to the mid thigh with knees pointing out. For a set of multiple reps you can take in air and adjust your breath after every rep or every two reps depending on your ability. However, try to do that during the time standing up from bottom position and finish breathing in before bringing the barbell to the hip position. In this way you will take in air more easily than having the barbell already at hip position. It does take some practice to get the timing and volume of air control right. 
#olympiclifting #jingyiweightlifting #techniquetuesday #strength #snatch #sports #weightlifting

Dumbbell/kettlebell row can be utilized in a reactive concentric way to train back muscle exclusiveness and consciousness that large muscle groups drive small muscle groups. 
1. Use hook grip for this exercise to relax forearms and engage back and lats firmly.
2. Keep neutral spine. 
3. Initiate the movement from back of shoulder and lats.
4. Pull the dumbbell to at the level of your chest. 
You can go much heavier than the body builder rows. In the video I was doing 50 kg dumbbell rows. Try it and comment below if you have any questions.

#olympiclifting #musclebuilding #strengthtraining #crossfit #workoutroutine

After seeing all the opinions from Tian Tao‚Äôs lasted instagram post I feel urged and necessary to clarify some myths. 
In the post from Coach Ma above the information is not true. According to Lv Xiaojun, Liao Hui and Long Qingquan, they have never told Ma about their future competitions. 
@tiantao85kg is opened and run by Tian Tao himself. The reason Tian Tao posted is that Ma Strength has been using large number of training videos from national weightlifting team for their commercial purpose. Coach Ma is our senior and contributed his part in international competitions. He should be respected. However he has crossed the line, not only use the personal and training videos and photos from those national team members for advertisements without even asking but also spread words that they never say, giving the public the wrong impression that he is very familiar with national team to gain more interest. In fact, regarding to his relation with Lv Xiaojun and Liao Hui they never wanted to be related with Coach Ma. Some of you may remember that Xiaojun, Liao Hui and their coach Yu indeed traveled to MA‚Äôs seminar but they are extremely regretted for this trip. 
I didn‚Äôt intend to comment anything before but thereafter Tian Tao‚Äôs act I would like to remind Coach Ma to focus more on coaching your athletes rather than over-advertising. 
#weightlifting #coaching

Behind the neck wide grip pull-up is one of the staple accessory exercises that we do at the end of training sessions. This exercise emphasizes a lot on the upper back muscles around the scapulae including Latissimus dorsi, Trapezius, Levator scapulae and Teres major. They are important muscle groups for extension and supporting the weight during lifting. Remember: 
1. Always perform this exercise after weightlifting or at least when your body is warmed up since this behind the neck position is an awkward position for the body. 
2. Keep the elbows down instead of backwards to protect the shoulder joints.
3. Return to the starting position on the bar from the top in a controlled fashion.
